### Tests (Q6) — deterministic, StubRunner + a call-counting Judge
- MISS (empty store): judge IS called (count==1); result written + re-readable;
  Reused=false; persisted doc has JudgeID + Seed set.
- HIT (identified judge): set a NON-EMPTY Pipeline.JudgeID on BOTH the seeding
  run and the query run; pre-seed a matching EvalResult (same targets, same
  non-empty JudgeID, same Seed); use a Judge double that increments-and-fails if
  invoked; assert judge NOT called, outcome from cached doc (same EvalID), NO new
  ref (List count unchanged), Reused=true.
- EMPTY active JudgeID (FIX 3): with Pipeline.JudgeID == "", even when an
  IDENTICAL prior eval doc exists, the cache is NOT consulted and the judge IS
  called (count==1, Reused=false, a new ref is written). No reuse for
  unidentified judges; the empty==empty hole stays closed.
- DIFFERENT targets -> MISS (different replay artifact sha): judge called.
- DIFFERENT known judge -> MISS: non-empty active id vs a different non-empty
  cached id => judge called.
- (also) non-empty active id vs empty-id cached doc -> MISS (no wildcard).
- DIFFERENT seed -> MISS: same targets + same non-empty JudgeID but different
  Seed => judge called. Same seed -> HIT.
- Seed presence: candidate doc with Seed==nil vs concrete-seed query -> MISS.
- --no-cache / Pipeline.Cache=false -> judge called even with a matching cached
  doc; new ref written.
- eval pkg: round-trip EvalResult with/without JudgeID and with/without Seed via
  JSON/ParseJSON; omitempty keeps pre-field bytes identical (backward-compat
  gate); Validate accepts empty JudgeID and absent Seed, rejects whitespace-only
  JudgeID.

